<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,478,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,412,478,503]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Oval-trigonal shell; rather pointed beaks; short, rounded posterior rostrum; hinge with a very small cardinal tooth in each valve; single thin radial ridge from the beaks to the postero-ventral margin; shallow radial depression posterior to the ridge, corresponding to an internal strong fold. Prodissoconch: shell type ST-2D; length about 130 µm; slightly inequilateral (longer anteriorly), ellipsoidal outline; convex profile; P-1 surface with arcuate wrinkles in the cicatrix area; P-2 almost absent; transition to the nepioconch rather well marked.
</paragraph>
